h3.div: The Frankfort-Elberta Area School District is located in Frankfort, Michigan in Benzie County and is nestled on the shores of Lake Michigan, 45 miles west of Traverse City. The school population for the 2019-2020 school year is 510 students, eager to learn. Educators are dedicated and caring and always look out for the student's best interest. M-STEP and standardized test scores are consistently above state and region averages.
*Our School Board welcomes community input at the monthly meetings. To see the schedule of upcoming board meetings visit the School Board page.
*Click here for the FEAS Continuity of Learning and COVID-19 Response Plan
*Interested in enrolling your child at Frankfort Elberta Area Schools? Click here for information!

div.class: hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc

h2.div: FHS and FEAS Alumni have challenged the Benzie Central Huskies and Glen Lake Lakers to the School Spirit Challenge!

iframe.aria-label: YouTube Video, FHS School Spirit Challenge
YouTube Video, FHS Alumni Panther Pride 2020

div.class: hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc

h3.div: Teachers and support staff continue to meet with their students in virtual discussions. We expect students to be actively engaged as learners by participating in discussions with their teachers, and completing assignments. Parents, we encourage you to check in often with your child and ask the question, “Show me what you have done this week for school.”
The food program saw 265 grocery bags leave the high school kitchen today. We have also received generous monetary donations from community members supporting the program.
Thank you Benzie Shores District Library for the donation of books that will be sent home to students in food bags very soon.
Third quarter report cards were put in the mail this past week. If you have questions about your child's report card, please call Ms. Gwaltney or Mr. Stapleton.

Hey FHS Seniors! Panther Parents are sponsoring banners to be hung on Main Street light poles in downtown Frankfort. The group is also honoring the class of 2020 with yard signs arriving at homes in the very near future.
Reminder to continue to check the district website for updated weekly information. Thank you and have a good weekend.
